1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
Hey Ryan, can I get you a pencil from the warehouse?

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:07,000
Uh, no thanks, I'm good.

3
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:09,000
Well that's okay, I'm going down.

4
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:13,000
Um, yeah, absolutely.

5
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:15,000
Alright, I'll be right back.

6
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:27,000
Woo! Awesome!

7
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:28,000
Thank you.

8
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:29,000
You're welcome.

9
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:31,000
Can you get me a pen from down in the warehouse?

10
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:33,000
Don't mind if I do.

11
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:35,000
See you in a minute.

12
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:37,000
Okay.

13
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:47,000
Woo!

14
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:49,000
There you go, fresh from the warehouse.

15
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:52,000
Hey Michael, would you get me some coffee from the warehouse?

16
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:54,000
There's coffee in the kitchen, Pam.

17
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:56,000
But the warehouse coffee tastes so much better.

18
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:58,000
Yes, it's better.

19
00:00:58,000 --> 00:00:59,000
Alright.

20
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:01,000
Okay.

21
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:14,000
I'm like Bette Midler in For the Boys.

22
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:16,000
I'm going to keep the troops entertained.

23
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:26,000
With cream and sugar?

24
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:28,000
Okay.

25
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:30,000
Alright.

26
00:01:56,000 --> 00:02:00,000
So I wanted to let you know that we lost Ed Truck.

27
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:04,000
Okay, let me see if I have his cell.

28
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:06,000
Is this the only reason you are calling, Jan?

29
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:08,000
Or does somebody miss me?

30
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:11,000
Michael, Ed died over the weekend.

31
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:14,000
Oh wow.

32
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:19,000
Yeah, and I know you with your boss, so I thought you should know.

33
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:21,000
Does his family know?

34
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:23,000
No, they don't.

35
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:25,000
I thought you should know.

36
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:27,000
Does his family know?

37
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:29,000
Yes, they know, Michael.

38
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:31,000
But I'm the first in the office.

39
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:34,000
I guess, yes.

40
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:40,000
I think it would be appropriate for you to make an announcement to your team in case they want to pay their respects.

41
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:43,000
Okay, yes, sure, I will do that.

42
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:49,000
As I am the first to find out, nobody else knows, and it is my responsibility to tell them.

43
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:50,000
Good.

44
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,000
How are you holding up?

45
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:53,000
Want me to come over?

46
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:59,000
Ed Truck died.

47
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:02,000
And it blows.

48
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:05,000
They say that with grief, time makes it worse.

49
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:11,000
Which is bad for me because I found out before anybody, so I've had more time to be sad.

50
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:12,000
Attention everybody.

51
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:18,000
I just received a call from corporate with some news that they felt that I should know first.

52
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:21,000
My old boss, Ed Truck, has died.

53
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:25,000
Oh, Michael, that's such terrible news.

54
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:27,000
You must feel so sad.

55
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:29,000
Yes, I am.

56
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:31,000
It's very sad.

57
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:34,000
Because he was my boss.

58
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:36,000
Well, that's a shame.

59
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,000
Ed was a good guy.

60
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:38,000
That's right.

61
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:39,000
You worked with him.

62
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:40,000
So did Creed.

63
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:44,000
Well, I'll be in my office in case anybody wants to drop by.

64
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:46,000
Cheer me up.

65
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:59,000
So did you hear the news?

66
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:01,000
The news that you just announced?

67
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:02,000
That Ed died?

68
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:03,000
Yeah.

69
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:04,000
Is there anything I can do?

70
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:06,000
Oh, gosh, what can anybody do?

71
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:07,000
Really?

72
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:09,000
He was almost 70.

73
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:11,000
Circle of life.

74
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:13,000
Yeah.

75
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:18,000
Oh, okay.

76
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:21,000
Yeah.

77
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:25,000
Okay.

78
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:29,000
Hey, Jimmy, want to see some pictures of my baby?

79
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Sure.

80
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:32,000
Here he is.

81
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:34,000
Oh, he's so cute.

82
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:35,000
And here's his first bath.

83
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:37,000
Warning contains nudity.

84
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,000
That's okay.

85
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,000
Oh, no, it's not.

86
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:40,000
I'm sorry.

87
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:42,000
Is that your husband in the tub with him?

88
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:46,000
You think we should have left our baby in the tub alone?

89
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:50,000
Talk to me when you have kids.

90
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:55,000
Sounds good.

91
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:59,000
What's going on with Fairfield County Schools?

92
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:01,000
Karen, did you generate that price list?

93
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:02,000
Shoot.

94
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:03,000
I don't know.

95
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:04,000
I don't know.

96
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:06,000
Okay, just get it done.

97
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:08,000
Jim, will you make sure?

98
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:11,000
Oh, yeah, definitely.

99
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:13,000
Suck up.

100
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:15,000
Josh, did you hear what I said?

101
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:21,000
Thank you, everyone.

102
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:24,000
Damn it.

103
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:26,000
What's up?

104
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:27,000
Nothing.

105
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:29,000
I'm just out of her...

106
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:30,000
Oh.

107
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:31,000
But don't worry about it.

108
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:35,000
My snack food doesn't fall under the umbrella of your authority.

109
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:38,000
That's where you're wrong.

110
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:41,000
I'm your project supervisor today.

111
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:44,000
And I have just decided that we're not doing anything

112
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:47,000
until you get the chips that you require.

113
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:49,000
So I think we should go get some.

114
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:52,000
Now, please.

115
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:54,000
Attention, everyone.

116
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:57,000
As you know, Ed Truck is dead.

117
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:59,000
If you have any contact information,

118
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:01,000
unroll the DEX files,

119
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:04,000
or in Microsoft Outlook, remove it now.

120
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:06,000
Also, if you have any photographs,

121
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:09,000
Pam will make her shredder available during lunch.

122
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:10,000
That is all.

123
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:12,000
It's a real shame about it, huh?

124
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:13,000
Yeah.

125
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:15,000
Must really have you thinking.

126
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:16,000
About what?

127
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:18,000
The older you get, the bigger the chances of you getting

128
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:19,000
a job.

129
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:21,000
I'm not sure.

130
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:22,000
About what?

131
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:25,000
The older you get, the bigger the chances you're gonna die.

132
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:26,000
You knew that.

133
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:28,000
Ed was decapitated.

134
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,000
What?

135
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:30,000
Really?

136
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,000
He was drunk as a skunk.

137
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:33,000
He was flying down Route 6.

138
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:36,000
He slides under an 18-wheeler, pop, it snaps right off.

139
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:38,000
Oh, my God.

140
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:40,000
That is the way to go.

141
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,000
Instant death.

142
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,000
Very smart.

143
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:45,000
You know, a human can go on living for several hours

144
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:47,000
after being decapitated.

145
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:49,000
You're thinking of a chicken.

146
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:51,000
What did I say?

147
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:54,000
That is just not the way a Dunder Mifflin manager should go.

148
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:55,000
I'm sorry.

149
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:57,000
Alone, out of the blue.

150
00:06:57,000 --> 00:07:00,000
He might even have his own head to comfort him.

151
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:04,000
So I'm not exactly sure how to say this.

152
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,000
Ed was decapitated.

153
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:06,000
What are you doing?

154
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:08,000
You said you didn't know how to say it.

155
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:09,000
I didn't.

156
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:15,000
He was driving on the road, and he went under a truck.

157
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:18,000
And that's when his head...
